    <div id="FAQs" class="section">
        <div class="faqs-box">
            <h2 class="section-title" style="padding-left: 200px;font-size: 2.8em;">FAQs</h2>
            <h3>1. Who is eligible to vote online?</h3>
            <p>All registered students in University who have a valid National Identity Card (NIC) and are listed in the
                enrolled students are eligible to vote online.</p>

            <h3>2. How do I register for online voting?</h3>
            <p>To register for online voting, Create an account and follow the instructions for online voter
                registration. You will need to provide your NIC number and other personal information to complete the
                registration.</p>

            <h3>3. What documents do I need to vote online?</h3>
            <p>You will need your NIC number and a valid email address to access the ElectionHub. Make sure your
                information is up-to-date and matches the records in the University.</p>

            <h3>4. How secure is the ElectionHub?</h3>
            <p>The online voting system uses state-of-the-art encryption and security measures to ensure the integrity
                and confidentiality of your vote. All data is securely transmitted and stored to prevent unauthorized
                access or tampering.</p>

            <h3>5. Can I change my vote after submitting it?</h3>
            <p>No, once you have submitted your vote, it cannot be changed. Make sure to review your choices carefully
                before finalizing your vote.</p>

            <h3>6. When will the election results be announced?</h3>
            <p>The election results will be announced by the Election Commission of Pakistan after the voting period has
                ended and all votes have been counted. Stay tuned to official ECP announcements for the latest updates.
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>

